* '''[[9 mai]] [[1950]]''' &mdash; Franchezikano Avrutno Ministro [[Robert Schuman]] anel lesko mangimos te avel ek phandli [[Europa]], janglo sar o [[mangimos Schuman]] dikhlyovel sar o shir la ekhe phandle Europyake.

* '''[[23 yuliyo]] [[1952]]''' &mdash; O Tratato andar le [[Pariz]]oste kerdilo o [[Europikano Khetanipen le Karbunosko thai le Sastryesko]] andar themende (po shirdipnaste) [[Benelux]], [[Luksemburgo]], [[Okchidentutni Jermaniya]], [[Franchiya]] thai [[Italiya]].
* '''[[1958]]''' &mdash; O EKhKS kerel o [[Europikano Kidipnasko Khetanipen]], savi, palal kodya avel o [[Europikano Khetanipen]] (EKh).

* '''[[1 Yanuara]] [[1973]] (Ekto buxlyarimos)''' &mdash; [[Danemarka]], [[Republika Irland]], thai [[Bari Britaniya]] kideren ando EKh.

* '''[[1 Yanuara]] [[1981]] (Duito buxlyarimos)''' &mdash; [[Grechiya]] avel ando EKh.

* '''[[1985]]''' &mdash; Granted [[home rule]] by Denmark six years earlier, [[Greenland]] decides to leave the EC following a [[referendum]]. See [[Special member state territories and their relations with the EU]] for details.

* '''[[1 January]] [[1986]] (Third Enlargement)''' &mdash; [[Spain]] and [[Portugal]] accede to the EC.

* '''[[3 October]] [[1990]]''' &mdash; [[East Germany]] and [[West Germany]] reunify (''see [[German reunification]]), automatically adding the former East Germany to the EC; reunification adds to the EC's area and population, but not the number of member states.

* '''[[1 November]] [[1993]]''' &mdash; The [[Maastricht Treaty]] takes effect, formally establishing the [[European Union]].

* '''[[1 January]] [[1995]] (Fourth Enlargement)''' &mdash; [[Austria]], [[Finland]], and [[Sweden]] accede to the EU.

* '''[[1 May]] [[2004]] (Fifth Enlargement, part I)''' {{rf|1|fifth}} &mdash; Comprising the largest number of countries ever admitted at one time, [[Cyprus]], the [[Czech Republic]], [[Estonia]], [[Hungary]], [[Latvia]], [[Lithuania]], [[Malta]], [[Poland]], [[Slovakia]], and [[Slovenia]] accede to the EU.


